div.p:
25 Ecclesiastical Censures, are Antichristian, such as the Cleargy hath inuented
for their owne preferment, to defend their malice, and multiply their couetousnesse:
It is not thus in my Booke, but I confesse it in substance.

All their arguments were of nothing but the reall presence in the Sacrament,
which point is already sufficiently argued in many places of this book, and will 
                     〈◊〉

more hereafter. If thou desire to sée the disputations, resort to the book at large;
for the Commissioners were so clamorous that they could not be suffered to speak,
as it appeareth by the report of Bishop Ridley.

sp.p:
We léese our labour, you seeke to put away all things that are told you
for your good, your Church no man can know: I said, yes that you may: He said,
I pray whereby.

It is not only an Indicatiue proposition, but an Imparatiue, or commaunding;
for he that said, This is my body, said also, take ye, eate ye; and except it bée
taken and eaten, the words (This is my body) can haue no verification.

div.p:
                  Robert Iohnson likewise would not aske the Quéen pardon, affirmed the Pope
to be the head of the Catholike Church, and would not say his prayers in English;
and when he had said them in Latine he died.
